column5: I've got a real bad itch that needs scratchin'. I'm thinking about a 3 day trip next month. I've heard this is a pretty good musky lake. Anybody been up there this time of year?
Our group will arrive on Saturday at Cedar Lake. We are staying at Cedar Point Lodge I know this is not September but I will post when I get back on how the fishing was.
have a camp on cedar.muskies can get big.had a buddie catch a 53incher fishing for walleyes a few years ago in october.cliff lake has biggies too.
www.acronymfinder.com/TTT.htmlNote: We have 190 other definitions for TTT in our Acronym Attic. new search; suggest new definition; Search for TTT in Online Dictionary Encyclopedia
ttt means "to the top". Used when you want your tread to come back to the front page.

I was not going to post, because we never go for musky. We go up opening weekend, and again the third week in September, for walleyes. We do extremely well in the fall. We talk to other guys, going after 'skies, they do well also. I used to fish them years ago, so I know that if you want big fish, go after them in fall. Use BIG bait, and you should produce. Weather can be nice, and it can be bad. Two years ago we had pretty good weather all week, but it turned at end of week. Our last day we fished in a white out, best fishing all week. Tight lines, go ahead and give it a try, I do not believe that you will be disappointed. We stay at Northern Lights Resort, they give you free bait there. That is a big bonus. There have been lots of 50" plus 'skies caught this summer, that should mean real good news for fall.
